quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  16,43,And We sent not before thee any but men unto whom We Revealed; so ask ye the people of the Admonition if ye know not
  16,44,"With evidences and scriptures We sent them. And We have sent down unto thee the Admonition that thou mayest expound unto mankind that which hath been revealed toward them, and that haply they may reflect"
  16,45,Feel then they secure who have plctted vices that Allah will not sink them into the earth or that the torment may come upon them whence they perceive not
  16,46,"Or, thathe will not take hold of them in their going to and fro! so that they cannot escape"
  16,47,"Or, that he will not take hold of them by giving them a fright? verily thy Lord is Kind, Merciful"
  16,48,"Have they not observed the things which Allah hath created? shadows thereof turn themselves on the right and on the left. prostrating themselves unto Allah, and they are lowly"
  16,49,And unto Allah prostrateth itself whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth of the living creatures and also the angels; and they are not stiff-necked
  16,50,They fear their Lord above them and do that which they are commanded
  16,51,"And Allah hath said: take not two gods; He is only One God so Me alone, Me dread"
  16,52,"And His is whatsoever is in the heavens and the earth, and unto Him is obedience due perpetually; will ye then fear any other than Allah"
  16,53,"And whatsoever of favours is with you is from Allah; then when distress toucheth you, unto Him ye cry out"
  16,54,"Then when He removeth the distress from you, forthwith a party of you with their Lord associate"